   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I'd argue that the current behavior is \"normal console behavior\":\n- when you are scrolled down, it will scroll down on appended text\n- when you manually scrolled up, it leaves the focus alone until you go to\n  the end again\n\nScrolling on append can be annoying when you're reading something in\nhistory and it suddenly jumps (currently not an issue as all output is a\ndirect response, but that will change when error/debug output is added).\n\nIf you want to add automatic scrolling to the end, do it when the user\nentered a command. This is similar to gnome-terminal etc.\n",
      "created_at" : "2012-05-14T07:53:18Z",
